            "description": "<br>The bamboo stalks are first cut and harvested, ready to be broken down where the bamboo get crushed mechanically to be broken down into cellulose. The cellulose is then dissolved into a solvent to create a liquid. The liquid is then extruded through the spinnerets to form fibres, whereby the fibres are then spun into yarn. Finally, the yarn is then woven or knitted into fabric.",
